cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.NE 

This paper is about a deep learning method for stereo matching, which involves computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also proposes a novel loss function and network architecture, which involves ML concepts such as self-supervised learning and self-improving ability. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories. Additionally, the paper deals with stereo matching, which is a robotics (RO) and computer graphics (CG) problem. Therefore, cs.RO and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also possible categories.
